    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="291"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d291">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 422.11G93/847</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Hartman</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s April 6. Investigation discloses that Railway interventor has stated
                    to two reliable persons his intention to bring suit and apply for receiver to
                    enable him to satisfy next Congress that he has obeyed resolution of last
                    Congress. However, I am credibly informed that he stated that if Mr. Norton will
                    consent to resume negotiations for private settlement on his return to Quito he
                    will not take legal action. It seems advisable that Mr. Norton consent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
